Four people are now recovering following injuries they sustained when a wall collapsed in Joburg. The incident happened while renovations where done at a house in Parkmore yesterday. Paramedics said that it was four construction workers who were left injured. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics found the group lying in a pile of rubble, surrounded by colleagues. “Paramedics assessed the men and found that all four had sustained minor to moderate injuries. "Paramedics treated the patients and provided one of them with pain-relief medication,” he added. The injured were then taken to Edenvale and Helen Joseph Hospital for further treatment.